WEBVTT

01:26.390 --> 01:35.020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.550 --> 01:37.810
[Episode 20]

01:38.870 --> 01:39.870
Be honest with me—

01:40.009 --> 01:41.450
in all the years we've known each other,

01:41.450 --> 01:42.780
have I ever scammed you?

01:42.810 --> 01:43.310
No.

01:44.150 --> 01:45.680
Have I ever scammed

01:45.680 --> 01:46.920
any of your friends?

01:47.000 --> 01:47.920
No.

01:48.350 --> 01:49.729
I'm reliable!

01:49.979 --> 01:51.110
You really haven't.

01:52.900 --> 01:53.700
Wait a minute.

01:53.729 --> 01:54.930
I'll turn the TV down.

01:57.479 --> 01:58.120
Well...

01:59.039 --> 02:00.160
Do you guys know

02:00.650 --> 02:02.480
how many people travel back and forth

02:02.480 --> 02:04.180
between China and Russia

02:04.200 --> 02:05.400
every year for trade?

02:05.650 --> 02:06.290
Do you know?

02:06.290 --> 02:06.840
No.

02:07.590 --> 02:08.440
100 thousand.

02:08.650 --> 02:10.050
Do you know how much money

02:10.120 --> 02:11.850
these 100,000 people generate

02:12.150 --> 02:12.800
in trade?

02:13.630 --> 02:14.410
We don't know that either.

02:14.410 --> 02:15.310
A billion or so?

02:15.970 --> 02:17.060
Forty billion.

02:17.900 --> 02:18.960
Forty billion?

02:19.530 --> 02:20.120
Do the math.

02:20.120 --> 02:21.500
If you divide this 40 billion among these

02:21.500 --> 02:22.190
100,000 people, how much

02:22.190 --> 02:23.050
can each person make?

02:23.050 --> 02:24.340
Seriously, if you go there now,

02:24.340 --> 02:26.090
you could make money
with your eyes closed.

02:26.090 --> 02:27.250
Even if you don't,

02:27.620 --> 02:29.490
just treat it as a trip.

02:29.579 --> 02:30.310
Go see Russia

02:30.400 --> 02:31.120
and expand your horizons—

02:31.120 --> 02:32.120
isn't that great?

02:33.810 --> 02:35.360
Making money sounds great.

02:35.500 --> 02:36.750
But if we go,

02:36.800 --> 02:38.460
where will we live? Is it safe?

02:39.180 --> 02:41.430
You'll definitely live better
than you do here.

02:41.430 --> 02:43.560
At least it won't be a basement, right?

02:43.810 --> 02:45.079
It'll be clean and hygienic.

02:45.079 --> 02:46.210
I have a buddy there.

02:46.470 --> 02:46.910
Everything

02:46.910 --> 02:48.440
will be arranged properly.

02:48.460 --> 02:49.190
How did you meet him?

02:49.190 --> 02:49.970
During his attempt to chase you down?

02:49.970 --> 02:51.740
Just shut up.

02:51.810 --> 02:53.079
You don't know how to talk.

02:53.079 --> 02:53.650
Jun.

02:53.750 --> 02:54.780
If we go there,

02:54.780 --> 02:56.510
how much can we make in one trip?

02:57.470 --> 02:59.600
The least I've made on my last few trips

02:59.800 --> 03:00.860
was 5 or 6 thousand.

03:01.000 --> 03:01.960
That much?

03:03.120 --> 03:03.930
Dollars.

03:05.960 --> 03:08.020
Shouldn't you earn rubles in Russia?

03:08.370 --> 03:09.310
You don't understand.

03:09.310 --> 03:12.040
International trade,
international currency.

03:14.130 --> 03:15.410
I do need money

03:15.460 --> 03:16.900
to record backing tracks.

03:16.900 --> 03:18.560
Don't we have backing tracks?

03:18.800 --> 03:21.660
The teacher said
they need to be more professional.

03:22.210 --> 03:22.740
Buddy.

03:23.810 --> 03:26.560
Looks like your two friends
are a little tempted.

03:28.060 --> 03:29.870
Don't think about anything else.

03:29.870 --> 03:30.870
Just work with me.

03:31.360 --> 03:33.090
You can't always
spend your family's money.

03:33.090 --> 03:35.400
If I were spending my family's money,

03:36.130 --> 03:37.400
would I live here?

03:39.060 --> 03:40.430
Well, you're not a little boy anymore.

03:40.430 --> 03:41.360
Don't you need to

03:41.370 --> 03:42.430
find a girlfriend?

03:43.800 --> 03:44.190
Jun.

03:48.360 --> 03:48.930
Did he...

03:50.570 --> 03:52.370
You just went through a breakup?

03:54.430 --> 03:55.960
That makes it even better.

03:56.400 --> 03:57.840
You need to make money even more now.

03:57.840 --> 03:58.560
Think about it.

03:58.560 --> 04:00.020
What do young girls want these days?

04:00.020 --> 04:00.430
Right?

04:00.840 --> 04:01.900
Are they after your looks?

04:01.900 --> 04:02.500
Unlikely.

04:02.620 --> 04:03.680
You look a bit goofy.

04:03.680 --> 04:04.870
not even as good-looking as me.

04:04.870 --> 04:07.080
They want a sense of security.

04:07.630 --> 04:08.710
That girl definitely ran off with someone

04:08.710 --> 04:09.620
because of money.

04:09.620 --> 04:10.620
You should just make money.

04:10.620 --> 04:12.090
Make as much as you can and piss her off.

04:12.090 --> 04:12.580
I'll do it.

04:12.580 --> 04:13.030
Do it!

04:13.120 --> 04:14.210
It's just my life.

04:14.240 --> 04:14.640
Right!

04:14.690 --> 04:15.310
I'll do it!

04:15.710 --> 04:17.630
I'll come back driving a fancy car too.

04:17.630 --> 04:18.890
Then the two of us will go too.

04:18.890 --> 04:20.490
It's safer with more people.

04:20.500 --> 04:21.540
Yeah, if the four of us go together,

04:21.540 --> 04:22.060
we can carry more goods

04:22.060 --> 04:23.460
on the way there and back.

04:23.810 --> 04:25.140
I'm the oldest among us.

04:25.180 --> 04:26.480
Let me get this out of the way first.

04:26.480 --> 04:27.950
Even brothers
must settle accounts clearly.

04:27.950 --> 04:28.620
We'll split the profit

04:28.620 --> 04:30.800
based on how much money we put in, okay?

04:31.040 --> 04:31.450
Okay.

04:32.240 --> 04:33.270
How much will you put in?

04:33.270 --> 04:34.770
I'll put in 2,000.

04:35.120 --> 04:35.620
And you?

04:36.250 --> 04:37.500
Then I'll put in 1,000.

04:37.500 --> 04:38.600
The two of us count as one.

04:38.600 --> 04:39.260
It's 3,000.

04:39.360 --> 04:39.810
Okay.

04:41.070 --> 04:42.400
How much will you put in?

04:42.700 --> 04:43.560
I'll put in 900.

04:43.690 --> 04:45.130
Is it enough to buy a train ticket?

04:45.130 --> 04:45.830
Of course.

04:46.720 --> 04:47.600
Those who put in more get more,

04:47.600 --> 04:48.420
those who put in less get less.

04:48.420 --> 04:49.680
But it doesn't matter.

04:49.740 --> 04:51.950
The important thing is that
we're doing this together!

04:51.950 --> 04:52.750
Come on, Jun.

04:52.810 --> 04:53.610
A toast to you.

04:54.430 --> 04:55.060
Come on.

04:55.890 --> 04:57.620
I wonder if you enjoyed the meal.

04:57.620 --> 04:58.870
We did.

04:59.180 --> 05:00.270
Let's meet again some other time.

05:00.270 --> 05:01.390
Okay.

05:08.100 --> 05:09.680
Mr. Chu is waiting for you?

05:12.920 --> 05:14.010
Oh, this child.

05:14.390 --> 05:16.120
If I had known you found

05:16.140 --> 05:17.340
someone like Mr. Chu,

05:17.720 --> 05:18.930
why would I have introduced

05:18.930 --> 05:20.060
this classmate to you?

05:20.060 --> 05:21.320
You didn't even ask

05:21.370 --> 05:22.370
how old he is

05:22.620 --> 05:24.420
or about his family background.

05:24.950 --> 05:27.740
What does his age matter?

05:29.160 --> 05:30.280
Didn't you say

05:30.390 --> 05:32.430
as long as he can handle the thing
in Beijing,

05:32.430 --> 05:33.360
it would be fine?

05:33.420 --> 05:34.360
Alright.

05:36.159 --> 05:36.860
I'm going back

05:36.860 --> 05:38.930
to pack your luggage.

05:41.390 --> 05:42.320
Mr. Chu!

05:42.890 --> 05:44.860
I won't bother you guys.

05:46.870 --> 05:47.430
Goodbye.

05:56.540 --> 05:57.540
Sorry about that.

05:57.870 --> 05:59.200
My mom is just like that.

05:59.420 --> 06:01.060
What's there to be sorry about?

06:01.060 --> 06:02.460
I think she's quite nice.

06:02.640 --> 06:03.240
Oh, right.

06:04.310 --> 06:05.720
I already booked the flight tickets.

06:05.720 --> 06:07.130
It's from Hangzhou to Beijing.

06:07.130 --> 06:08.590
If you're eager to return,

06:08.890 --> 06:09.870
we can fly back.

06:10.070 --> 06:10.810
Otherwise,

06:11.390 --> 06:12.560
I have another suggestion.

06:12.560 --> 06:14.020
I want to return to Beijing

06:14.060 --> 06:16.120
and Seasons Change Hostel
as soon as possible.

06:16.120 --> 06:16.810
Thank you.

06:17.390 --> 06:18.990
Then we will take the flight.

06:34.060 --> 06:36.710
Don't go. Just stay at home.

06:37.250 --> 06:39.270
I don't want to hear any sounds.

06:39.860 --> 06:41.000
I just want to live

06:41.500 --> 06:42.770
like this every day.

06:44.870 --> 06:49.980
I don't want to go either.

06:51.270 --> 06:53.390
I also want to

06:53.450 --> 06:55.930
be with my wife and kid every day.

06:56.860 --> 06:58.520
But I'm halfway through this.

06:58.560 --> 06:59.620
If you make me stop,

06:59.630 --> 07:00.800
I'll feel bad.

07:02.800 --> 07:04.220
A family of three is complete

07:04.220 --> 07:06.930
and content.

07:09.250 --> 07:11.890
Give me one more year. Just one year.

07:14.120 --> 07:15.160
Just one year?

07:15.690 --> 07:16.450
One year.

07:46.890 --> 07:47.450
Cao Ye.

07:51.390 --> 07:51.950
Cao Ye.

07:57.950 --> 07:58.500
Cao Ye.

08:11.240 --> 08:12.120
Cao Ye!

08:24.630 --> 08:24.980
Dad.

08:26.450 --> 08:27.710
I went back to Beijing.

08:28.980 --> 08:30.780
The lanterns have been painted.

08:31.540 --> 08:33.240
But I won't paint anymore.

08:33.870 --> 08:34.470
I'm tired.

08:35.909 --> 08:37.510
I should have listened to you

08:37.630 --> 08:39.030
and been more practical.

08:39.860 --> 08:40.980
As for dreams,

08:41.549 --> 08:43.740
some people can reach them
just by standing on tiptoe,

08:43.740 --> 08:46.670
while others
can never touch them in their lifetime.

08:48.940 --> 08:49.220
Dad,

08:50.290 --> 08:51.280
only money

08:51.500 --> 08:52.480
can make it so we

08:52.510 --> 08:55.110
no longer have to look
at other people's faces.

08:56.700 --> 08:57.180
Dad,

08:58.320 --> 09:00.520
I've decided to change my way of living.

09:00.670 --> 09:01.870
Wait for my good news.

09:12.130 --> 09:12.860
Ranran?

09:13.790 --> 09:16.160
Northeasterner? Happy New Year.

09:16.260 --> 09:17.240
Happy New Year. Happy New Year.

09:17.240 --> 09:18.630
Why are you back so early?

09:18.630 --> 09:19.890
I missed you guys.

09:20.100 --> 09:21.030
You missed us?

09:23.120 --> 09:24.580
Train tickets to Beijing

09:24.580 --> 09:25.250
are hard to buy now.

09:25.250 --> 09:26.290
How did you get one?

09:26.290 --> 09:27.690
I asked a friend for help.

09:27.750 --> 09:29.750
Your friend must be pretty capable.

09:30.100 --> 09:31.270
Where are they?

09:31.360 --> 09:32.320
Are they back?

09:33.890 --> 09:35.290
You mean Tao Liangliang?

09:35.340 --> 09:36.540
I mean Zhuang Zhuang.

09:37.910 --> 09:39.240
Zhuang Zhuang, Liangliang,

09:39.240 --> 09:40.030
and Xu Shengli.

09:40.030 --> 09:40.910
The three of them

09:40.910 --> 09:42.970
went off with a scalper from Beijing.

09:43.630 --> 09:44.550
Where did they go?

09:44.550 --> 09:45.250
Russia.

09:46.770 --> 09:48.180
Why did they go to Russia?

09:48.600 --> 09:50.000
To make money, of course.

09:50.320 --> 09:50.650
Do you think

09:50.650 --> 09:52.180
they went to Russia for fun?

09:52.370 --> 09:53.200
Let me tell you,

09:53.200 --> 09:54.660
anyone who knows anything

09:54.820 --> 09:55.840
knows that

09:55.840 --> 09:57.640
reselling in Russia isn't easy.

10:12.320 --> 10:13.650
Take a rest.

10:13.740 --> 10:14.270
I'm fine.

10:15.460 --> 10:16.100
Jun.

10:17.910 --> 10:19.220
My back is breaking.

10:20.150 --> 10:22.360
I paid for this train ticket.

10:22.480 --> 10:24.310
I wanted to get some solid sleep.

10:24.410 --> 10:24.840
Now,

10:24.870 --> 10:26.840
I haven't had a good sleep in three days.

10:26.840 --> 10:27.630
Have a seat.

10:27.630 --> 10:28.800
It's fine. Go ahead.

10:28.870 --> 10:29.550
Hurry.

10:31.620 --> 10:32.630
I can't straighten my back

10:32.630 --> 10:34.080
or my legs.

10:36.460 --> 10:37.600
When will we arrive?

10:39.700 --> 10:40.610
Jun?

10:41.050 --> 10:42.710
I only slept for a short while.

10:42.860 --> 10:44.060
Keep your mouth shut.

10:44.080 --> 10:45.150
We'll be there soon.

10:45.150 --> 10:46.150
You talk too much.

10:46.750 --> 10:48.080
We haven't arrived yet,

10:48.080 --> 10:49.200
and we can't go back either.

10:49.200 --> 10:50.530
If you throw me out of the train,

10:50.530 --> 10:52.100
I wouldn't even know where I am.

10:52.100 --> 10:53.030
I can't even sleep.

10:53.030 --> 10:53.530
Right now,

10:53.530 --> 10:54.890
I'm sleeping here

10:54.890 --> 10:56.090
with a bunch of sacks.

10:56.340 --> 10:57.240
You are really...

10:57.240 --> 10:58.040
How could I...

10:58.220 --> 10:59.360
bring you out?

10:59.410 --> 11:00.630
These sacks are almost pushing me

11:00.630 --> 11:01.870
off the bed.

11:01.910 --> 11:03.290
Th-The place you're at now

11:03.290 --> 11:05.050
is... is called Blagoveshchensk.

11:05.050 --> 11:06.240
Do you know where it is?

11:06.240 --> 11:07.320
Do you understand now that I've told you?

11:07.320 --> 11:08.620
Just take a nap.

11:08.620 --> 11:10.280
We still have work to do later.

11:10.790 --> 11:12.060
Be careful.

11:12.290 --> 11:12.960
Come on. M-

11:13.340 --> 11:14.100
Me? Be careful?

11:14.100 --> 11:15.900
I have more than 10 sacks up here.

11:16.230 --> 11:18.510
When have I ever suffered like this?

11:21.390 --> 11:22.180
Hurry up

11:22.530 --> 11:23.650
and cut the crap.

11:24.170 --> 11:25.150
Get some sleep

11:25.440 --> 11:26.320
to save your energy.

11:26.320 --> 11:27.650
-We have work to do.
-There are eggs.

11:27.650 --> 11:28.290
Get an egg.

11:28.370 --> 11:29.150
How can I sleep?

11:29.150 --> 11:30.720
It's full of luggage up here.

11:30.720 --> 11:32.640
There's no room for me at all.

11:32.720 --> 11:33.720
Then don't sleep.

11:34.820 --> 11:35.910
I was thinking of

11:36.010 --> 11:36.910
taking you out to have fun.

11:36.910 --> 11:37.770
I didn't expect

11:38.480 --> 11:40.130
that it would turn into a cargo run.

11:40.130 --> 11:42.000
We came out
to do business in the first place.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.440
It's already good enough.

11:43.440 --> 11:44.600
These instant noodles are so delicious.

11:44.600 --> 11:45.130
You eat.

12:05.500 --> 12:06.000
Stop sleeping! Stop sleeping!

12:06.000 --> 12:06.910
There's going to be a war!

12:06.910 --> 12:07.740
There's going to be a war!

12:07.740 --> 12:08.720
Listen to my command.

12:08.720 --> 12:11.100
Your eyes must be sharp,
your hands must be fast,

12:11.100 --> 12:12.240
and your legs must be diligent. Got it?

12:12.240 --> 12:12.770
Later...

12:13.120 --> 12:14.690
My legs are numb.

12:14.790 --> 12:15.370
Let's go. Let's go.

12:15.370 --> 12:16.480
-What's happening?
-Get off! Get off!

12:16.480 --> 12:18.010
Well, give me what...

12:18.480 --> 12:20.280
Give me what I tell you to give me!

12:32.010 --> 12:32.870
Excuse me!

12:33.000 --> 12:33.600
Excuse me!

12:33.620 --> 12:35.100
Open the window! Open the window!

12:35.100 --> 12:36.100
Here, let me do it!

12:36.150 --> 12:37.750
Open the window! Open the window!

12:37.750 --> 12:39.150
That one! I want that one!

12:41.620 --> 12:42.630
Right away!

12:44.240 --> 12:46.600
Three hundred a sack!
Three hundred a sack!

12:46.600 --> 12:47.320
Good stuff!

12:48.010 --> 12:49.050
Good stuff!

12:49.170 --> 12:49.940
Good stuff!

12:56.740 --> 12:59.070
Take whichever you like!

12:59.130 --> 13:00.530
Take whichever you like!

13:01.650 --> 13:03.320
Good stuff!

13:04.370 --> 13:05.220
Careful! Careful!

13:05.220 --> 13:05.890
Take a look!

13:52.850 --> 13:53.530
Jun.

13:53.890 --> 13:55.080
Get some sleep after you eat,

13:55.080 --> 13:56.140
and get a good rest.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.580
You guys should eat something quickly

13:58.580 --> 13:59.170
to regain your energy.

13:59.170 --> 14:00.500
There are 2 stops ahead.

14:01.460 --> 14:03.030
He's yelled himself hoarse.

14:03.030 --> 14:04.530
This trip is like fighting a war.

14:04.530 --> 14:06.530
I've never seen anything like this.

14:06.700 --> 14:08.150
Money was falling like rain,

14:08.150 --> 14:09.670
just pouring down.

14:09.820 --> 14:10.750
It was unbelievable.

14:10.750 --> 14:11.840
As the saying goes,

14:12.130 --> 14:14.520
"Time is money." Right?

14:14.750 --> 14:15.270
Look.

14:15.270 --> 14:15.840
We've verified that

14:15.840 --> 14:16.650
time is money.

14:17.440 --> 14:18.770
We just earned all this.

14:19.010 --> 14:20.320
Let's count it out by our shares

14:20.320 --> 14:21.220
and split it.

14:21.910 --> 14:23.640
We're splitting it right here?

14:24.630 --> 14:25.290
Right here.

14:25.550 --> 14:27.080
We split it every time we earn a batch,

14:27.080 --> 14:28.810
so we don't get confused later.

14:29.720 --> 14:30.980
It was such a short while

14:30.980 --> 14:32.270
and we earned this much.

14:32.270 --> 14:33.870
We're not even in Moscow yet.

14:35.100 --> 14:37.000
You can count on Mr. Lucky for good luck.

14:37.000 --> 14:38.500
We'll earn money from here to Moscow,

14:38.500 --> 14:40.430
and then earn more all the way back.

14:41.200 --> 14:42.030
Jun, if I had known it would be like this,

14:42.030 --> 14:42.870
I would have asked

14:42.870 --> 14:44.100
all my relatives

14:44.910 --> 14:46.770
to borrow money to invest in this.

14:47.240 --> 14:48.300
Regret it now, huh?

14:49.150 --> 14:51.210
You only paid for your train tickets.

14:51.290 --> 14:52.600
You should have put in more money.

14:52.600 --> 14:53.440
Remember what I said earlier

14:53.440 --> 14:54.240
about the three key points?

14:54.240 --> 14:54.970
Repeat them.

14:55.500 --> 14:57.250
Your eyes must be sharp,
your hands must be fast...

14:57.250 --> 14:59.130
Your eyes must be sharp,
your hands must be fast,

14:59.130 --> 14:59.720
and your legs must be diligent.

14:59.720 --> 15:00.120
Right.

15:00.240 --> 15:01.370
Sharp, fast and diligent.

15:01.370 --> 15:02.770
Remember these three points.

15:02.770 --> 15:04.500
The four of us will work together as one,

15:04.500 --> 15:06.300
charge forward, and make money!

15:06.320 --> 15:07.620
We will make a fortune!

15:07.720 --> 15:08.720
We will make a fortune!

15:08.720 --> 15:09.980
We will make a fortune!

15:11.250 --> 15:12.180
Let me take a sip.

15:12.240 --> 15:13.340
Take it. Here.

15:14.030 --> 15:14.770
Let me take a sip.

15:14.770 --> 15:15.910
Eat something too. Get some energy.

15:15.910 --> 15:17.050
I'm starving, really.

15:17.050 --> 15:17.940
There are eggs.

15:18.000 --> 15:18.530
There are eggs.

15:18.530 --> 15:19.630
-In that blue bag.
-Where are the eggs?

15:19.630 --> 15:20.790
-The blue bag?
-Yes.

15:21.460 --> 15:23.860
Why didn't you say
there were eggs earlier?

15:24.390 --> 15:29.660
[Moscow]

15:57.770 --> 15:58.570
Wait a moment.

15:58.890 --> 16:00.420
The train is arriving soon.

16:00.700 --> 16:01.260
Jun.

16:01.600 --> 16:02.630
Did we sell all our big and small sacks

16:02.630 --> 16:04.130
on the train?

16:05.120 --> 16:06.270
Six days on the train

16:06.440 --> 16:07.340
made each of us ten thousand?

16:07.340 --> 16:08.490
That's awesome.

16:08.550 --> 16:09.710
A scalper

16:09.940 --> 16:11.200
means you can make money

16:11.200 --> 16:11.860
both going and returning.

16:11.860 --> 16:12.790
That's called a scalper.

16:12.790 --> 16:14.240
Playing that crappy saxophone of yours—

16:14.240 --> 16:15.340
only exhaling without inhaling—

16:15.340 --> 16:16.170
how's that supposed to work?

16:16.170 --> 16:17.710
We profit both ways.

16:17.740 --> 16:18.890
You're really good at doing business.

16:18.890 --> 16:20.220
Now that they're all sold out,

16:20.220 --> 16:21.270
what do we sell?

16:21.740 --> 16:22.340
My

16:22.360 --> 16:23.550
big brain

16:23.550 --> 16:24.610
is full of wisdom.

16:24.980 --> 16:25.750
Before coming here,

16:25.750 --> 16:27.080
I had my buddy in Beijing

16:27.650 --> 16:29.070
send a batch of goods over.

16:29.070 --> 16:30.630
Jeans and thermal underwear.

16:30.630 --> 16:31.500
We just need to pick them up.

16:31.500 --> 16:32.250
Then when we came here,

16:32.250 --> 16:34.050
why didn't we bring them with us?

16:34.460 --> 16:35.620
Even with four of us,

16:35.650 --> 16:36.840
we still couldn't carry them all.

16:36.840 --> 16:37.530
For such a large batch of goods,

16:37.530 --> 16:38.550
we need a truck.

16:38.650 --> 16:40.250
I figured we shouldn't come empty-handed.

16:40.250 --> 16:40.600
Right?

16:40.600 --> 16:41.320
On the way back and forth,

16:41.320 --> 16:42.460
we can just carry some stuff to sell.

16:42.460 --> 16:42.980
Once we get off the train,

16:42.980 --> 16:44.510
we'll sell the large batch.

16:44.650 --> 16:46.130
Will we still sell at the train station?

16:46.130 --> 16:46.710
No.

16:46.790 --> 16:48.080
We need to go to the big market.

16:48.080 --> 16:49.500
In Russia, there are special

16:49.500 --> 16:51.150
big markets provided for Chinese

16:51.150 --> 16:52.370
to sell goods

16:52.410 --> 16:53.140
to Russians.

16:53.150 --> 16:55.440
Only those big markets
can bring in big money.

16:55.440 --> 16:57.410
You three have to make a decision.

16:58.320 --> 16:59.130
Do you want to come here

16:59.130 --> 16:59.990
just to travel,

17:00.010 --> 17:02.170
or follow Mr. Lucky to try your luck—

17:02.250 --> 17:03.460
put in the little money you earned

17:03.460 --> 17:05.250
and let's make big money together?

17:05.250 --> 17:06.569
Of course we'll keep doing it.

17:06.569 --> 17:08.829
Who wouldn't want to make big money
with little money?

17:08.829 --> 17:09.829
We're all in.

17:09.940 --> 17:12.339
Let's do it.
Treat it as experiencing life.

17:12.720 --> 17:13.530
Doing business here,

17:13.530 --> 17:14.810
you all need to be careful.

17:14.810 --> 17:16.000
There are all kinds of people.

17:16.000 --> 17:17.950
And some will scam anyone.

17:18.270 --> 17:19.790
We made it here

17:20.000 --> 17:21.109
safely.

17:21.400 --> 17:22.250
As the oldest among us,

17:22.250 --> 17:23.310
I'm responsible for getting all of us

17:23.310 --> 17:24.490
back safely.

17:24.589 --> 17:25.430
Understood?

17:25.609 --> 17:26.420
Whatever you do,

17:26.420 --> 17:28.140
be extremely careful.

17:29.000 --> 17:29.860
Follow my lead.

17:30.700 --> 17:31.750
My throat is really giving out.

17:31.750 --> 17:33.350
I'll buy a Kvass to soothe it.

17:34.070 --> 17:35.000
Stay close to me.

17:38.140 --> 17:38.810
Let's go. Hurry up.

17:38.810 --> 17:39.480
Let's go.

17:44.330 --> 17:44.990
We're here.

17:45.550 --> 17:46.610
Sir, please wait a moment.

17:46.610 --> 17:47.850
We need to get our luggage.

17:47.850 --> 17:49.070
This is my friend's house.

17:49.070 --> 17:50.800
It's cheaper than hotel rooms.

17:50.880 --> 17:52.090
The environment is nice,

17:52.090 --> 17:54.020
and it's comfortable to stay here.

17:54.220 --> 17:55.940
Although it's a bit far from the city,

17:55.940 --> 17:56.660
we can borrow this car

17:56.660 --> 17:57.770
every now and then

17:57.940 --> 17:59.180
to carry some goods or something.

17:59.180 --> 18:00.180
It's pretty good.

18:00.460 --> 18:01.380
Sophia!

18:01.510 --> 18:02.810
This house is pretty nice.

18:02.810 --> 18:03.460
It looks so big.

18:03.460 --> 18:04.680
-Sophia!
-It's quite pretty.

18:04.680 --> 18:06.020
Sophia!

18:07.310 --> 18:08.200
Jun!

18:08.240 --> 18:11.460
Sophia, Sophia, Sophia!

18:12.960 --> 18:14.120
We meet again!

18:16.650 --> 18:17.710
Let me kiss you too.

18:24.010 --> 18:26.050
-It's cold. Get in.
-Let's go inside.

18:26.050 --> 18:27.460
How have you been lately?

18:27.500 --> 18:28.590
I'm doing well.

18:28.590 --> 18:30.520
It's been so long since we last met.

18:30.830 --> 18:31.290
Well...

18:32.350 --> 18:34.360
Should we go in now?

18:34.810 --> 18:36.350
The thing is, we don't even know

18:36.350 --> 18:38.440
what the situation is right now.

18:41.090 --> 18:41.460
Here.

18:41.830 --> 18:42.200
Have some tea.

18:42.200 --> 18:43.000
Hello. Hello.

18:43.920 --> 18:44.320
Hello.

18:45.720 --> 18:46.270
Don't...

18:46.500 --> 18:47.810
Don't trouble yourself.

18:47.810 --> 18:50.270
Pour it yourself if you want some.
It's fine.

18:50.420 --> 18:51.620
Let me introduce you.

18:52.640 --> 18:53.380
Sophia.

18:53.720 --> 18:54.420
She is...

19:01.900 --> 19:03.310
is... is my best friend.

19:03.460 --> 19:04.990
We're really really close.

19:06.330 --> 19:06.810
Jun...

19:07.530 --> 19:09.790
Then why did you kiss each other just now?

19:10.180 --> 19:11.350
That was etiquette.

19:11.420 --> 19:12.140
Do you understand?

19:12.140 --> 19:13.110
It's local etiquette.

19:13.110 --> 19:13.830
Hillbilly.

19:14.640 --> 19:16.560
Um... This is Shengli.

19:17.290 --> 19:18.790
-Hello.
-And Zhuang Zhuang.

19:18.790 --> 19:19.240
Hello.

19:19.350 --> 19:21.080
Jun. He's my childhood friend.

19:21.640 --> 19:22.640
My name is not Jun.

19:22.950 --> 19:24.440
It's Liangliang.
Liangliang is my childhood friend.

19:24.440 --> 19:24.980
You don't understand.

19:24.980 --> 19:25.850
I'll explain it to you later.

19:25.850 --> 19:27.680
And this time,

19:27.770 --> 19:28.550
I brought them along

19:28.550 --> 19:29.570
to see the world.

19:29.740 --> 19:32.220
And to make some money together.

19:32.250 --> 19:32.920
Hello, Sister-in-law.

19:32.920 --> 19:33.640
Hello.

19:34.510 --> 19:35.270
Jun's friends

19:35.270 --> 19:36.630
are my friends.

19:36.880 --> 19:39.400
Welcome to Russia.

19:40.000 --> 19:41.330
Your Chinese is so good.

19:41.400 --> 19:42.790
Her Chinese is very good.

19:42.790 --> 19:43.310
Sit.

19:43.310 --> 19:44.370
Let's sit and talk.

19:45.530 --> 19:46.840
No... It's fine.

19:46.980 --> 19:47.980
It's fine. I can just

19:47.980 --> 19:48.910
tell you

19:49.030 --> 19:49.750
how I

19:49.750 --> 19:51.440
met Sophia.

19:52.030 --> 19:53.700
Relax. Just relax.

19:54.270 --> 19:55.000
I am relaxed.

19:55.440 --> 19:56.570
What are you saying?

19:57.010 --> 19:57.810
I was...

19:58.790 --> 19:59.640
Well... At first,

19:59.640 --> 20:00.770
I came

20:00.770 --> 20:02.090
to Russia alone to do business.

20:02.090 --> 20:02.920
I was new here

20:03.000 --> 20:04.610
and unfamiliar with the place.

20:04.610 --> 20:05.350
That day, I happened to be stopped

20:05.350 --> 20:06.210
for an ID check,

20:06.420 --> 20:07.240
and I didn't have my ID with me.

20:07.240 --> 20:08.710
I couldn't explain myself clearly

20:08.710 --> 20:09.920
and ended up gesturing a lot.

20:09.920 --> 20:11.160
They didn't know what I was doing,

20:11.160 --> 20:12.810
and insisted on taking me away.

20:12.810 --> 20:15.590
Right at the moment
they were about to take me away,

20:15.590 --> 20:16.290
I heard

20:16.290 --> 20:17.590
a heavenly voice—

20:21.850 --> 20:23.200
"What are you doing?

20:23.610 --> 20:24.850
I can speak Chinese."

20:26.200 --> 20:27.400
When I turned around,

20:27.400 --> 20:29.260
I saw Sophia standing against the light.

20:29.260 --> 20:31.060
The sunlight was shining on her,

20:31.270 --> 20:32.330
golden and bright,

20:32.350 --> 20:33.610
like an angel

20:34.010 --> 20:35.210
descending to earth.

20:35.510 --> 20:37.440
She spoke in her standard Mandarin

20:37.460 --> 20:38.110
and saved my life.

20:38.110 --> 20:39.000
Now, whenever I talk about it—

20:39.000 --> 20:40.500
look—I get goosebumps.

20:40.790 --> 20:41.990
Thank you. Thank you.

20:42.830 --> 20:45.090
This story deserves a round of applause.

20:48.000 --> 20:48.690
I run a

20:48.830 --> 20:51.050
handicraft business in Russia.

20:51.350 --> 20:53.110
After I met Jun,

20:53.140 --> 20:54.250
I started selling

20:54.530 --> 20:56.050
my crafts to China.

20:56.830 --> 20:57.610
So knowing him

20:57.610 --> 20:58.770
is truly my luck.

20:59.460 --> 21:01.480
Meeting you is also my luck

21:01.480 --> 21:02.410
for 8 lifetimes.

21:02.810 --> 21:04.670
My ancestors must be blessing me.

21:09.680 --> 21:10.790
Didn't you say

21:10.790 --> 21:12.160
you love Chinese tea?

21:13.640 --> 21:15.480
I asked someone
to get this specially for you.

21:15.480 --> 21:16.770
Yunnan Dahongpao.

21:17.110 --> 21:18.710
And Maojian. It's green tea.

21:19.040 --> 21:19.800
[Tea]

21:19.200 --> 21:19.770
And this.

21:20.160 --> 21:21.550
You definitely haven't seen this before.

21:21.550 --> 21:22.750
As we say in Beijing,

21:23.030 --> 21:24.910
it's absolutely fantastic.

21:25.070 --> 21:26.330
Daoxiangcun pastries.

21:26.330 --> 21:26.960
Have a taste.

21:26.960 --> 21:28.460
If you like them,
I'll bring them to you every time.

21:28.460 --> 21:30.140
Such a beautiful box. Look.

21:30.220 --> 21:31.660
I also brought 2 bottles of liquor.

21:31.660 --> 21:33.070
Last time
when we were drinking your vodka,

21:33.070 --> 21:34.140
I couldn't outdrink you

21:34.140 --> 21:35.270
and ended up throwing up
all over your carpet.

21:35.270 --> 21:35.990
So sorry about that.

21:35.990 --> 21:37.180
This time I brought 2 bottles of Erguotou.

21:37.180 --> 21:37.910
Have a taste.

21:38.140 --> 21:39.740
Let's have another contest.

21:39.900 --> 21:41.030
-And…
-46% alcohol.

21:41.920 --> 21:42.310
And...

21:42.310 --> 21:43.500
She even knows it's 46% alcohol.

21:43.500 --> 21:45.200
I bought this lambskin coat for you

21:45.200 --> 21:46.880
at the mall.

21:47.250 --> 21:48.510
It's mink fur.

21:48.590 --> 21:49.500
I didn't know your size.

21:49.500 --> 21:50.460
So I just guessed.

21:50.460 --> 21:51.180
Try it on.

21:51.260 --> 21:52.260
See if you like it.

21:52.400 --> 21:53.270
I was afraid you might not like this one,

21:53.270 --> 21:54.740
so I bought you two more.

21:55.000 --> 21:56.400
But here's a funny thing.

21:56.420 --> 21:57.980
After I bought it, I took a look.

21:57.980 --> 21:59.710
It was actually made in Russia.

22:00.290 --> 22:01.100
And then I...

22:01.740 --> 22:02.590
It's so embarrassing.

22:02.590 --> 22:03.310
But it's fine.

22:03.310 --> 22:04.270
Wear them if you like them.

22:04.270 --> 22:05.130
And...

22:05.550 --> 22:06.420
if you need more,

22:06.420 --> 22:07.160
I'll buy more for you.

22:07.160 --> 22:07.770
More?

22:07.770 --> 22:08.960
Come on, you brought

22:08.960 --> 22:10.290
so many gifts this time.

22:10.420 --> 22:11.700
You helped me so much.
It's the least I could do.

22:11.700 --> 22:13.700
And you remember I like Chinese tea.

22:17.740 --> 22:18.310
Oh right.

22:18.940 --> 22:20.870
I've arranged rooms for all of you.

22:20.940 --> 22:22.190
Jun told me

22:22.270 --> 22:23.960
there's a young couple.

22:23.960 --> 22:24.690
Is that true?

22:28.960 --> 22:29.660
Then I just happen

22:29.660 --> 22:31.390
to have 2 rooms available here.

22:34.160 --> 22:35.180
No, no. No need.

22:35.570 --> 22:36.570
One room for the lady,

22:36.570 --> 22:37.460
and then...

22:39.900 --> 22:41.000
The two of us will share a room.

22:41.000 --> 22:41.500
One for her,

22:41.500 --> 22:42.300
and one for us.

22:43.810 --> 22:44.680
Aren't you staying?

22:44.680 --> 22:45.220
I am.

22:45.250 --> 22:45.660
Sister-in-law.

22:45.660 --> 22:45.880
He's not...

22:45.880 --> 22:46.720
You and Jun

22:46.720 --> 22:47.400
can share a room.

22:47.400 --> 22:48.570
You haven't seen each other
for a long time...

22:48.570 --> 22:49.440
Shut up!

22:49.960 --> 22:51.380
You never know when to shut up!

22:51.380 --> 22:51.810
I'm just trying to help.

22:51.810 --> 22:52.870
W-We really are...

22:53.050 --> 22:55.220
We are just friends, you know?

22:55.290 --> 22:56.220
Friends. You...

22:56.510 --> 22:58.570
You're making inappropriate jokes.

22:58.700 --> 23:00.440
He's usually not good at joking.

23:00.440 --> 23:01.300
Don't mind him.

23:01.810 --> 23:03.700
Then where will you stay?

23:04.000 --> 23:04.500
The...

23:04.500 --> 23:05.610
The three of us will share a room.

23:05.610 --> 23:06.380
The three of us.

23:06.380 --> 23:07.240
It's fine.

23:07.700 --> 23:08.050
Okay.

23:08.660 --> 23:09.590
It was a misunderstanding.

23:09.590 --> 23:09.980
Oh, right.

23:09.980 --> 23:10.500
Later, well...

23:10.500 --> 23:12.330
can we... borrow your car again?

23:12.510 --> 23:14.530
We need to go get some goods

23:14.570 --> 23:15.750
to sell at the market tomorrow.

23:15.750 --> 23:17.000
I hope it's not a bother.

23:17.000 --> 23:17.800
Of course not.

23:17.900 --> 23:19.500
The key is at the usual place.

23:19.800 --> 23:21.590
Then let's go now, shall we?

23:21.770 --> 23:22.400
Wait a minute.

23:22.400 --> 23:24.330
Well, you guys go ahead.

23:24.330 --> 23:26.010
I haven't rested well these past two days.

23:26.010 --> 23:27.180
I'll rest early today

23:27.180 --> 23:28.770
to recharge and get ready.

23:28.770 --> 23:29.880
My back feels a bit tight.

23:29.880 --> 23:31.510
He's just full of excuses.

23:31.570 --> 23:32.960
Alright. Then you just rest.

23:32.960 --> 23:33.770
Well, Zhuang Zhuang,

23:33.770 --> 23:34.500
you should rest too.

23:34.500 --> 23:35.280
I'll go with you.

23:35.280 --> 23:36.740
No need. The two of us will do.

23:36.740 --> 23:37.180
Okay.

23:37.180 --> 23:38.050
Are you sure?

23:38.220 --> 23:38.740
Yes.

23:38.750 --> 23:39.580
Then we...

23:39.750 --> 23:41.410
Then let's go.

23:41.610 --> 23:42.790
You don't need to wait for us.

23:42.790 --> 23:44.010
Get some rest if you want.

23:44.010 --> 23:44.610
It's fine.

23:44.640 --> 23:45.160
Um...

23:45.160 --> 23:45.660
Be safe.

23:45.660 --> 23:46.590
Shut your mouth!

23:47.090 --> 23:47.660
I'm helping you!

23:47.660 --> 23:48.180
Don't make stupid jokes!

23:48.180 --> 23:48.720
Be safe.

23:48.720 --> 23:49.920
You're ruining my reputation.

23:49.920 --> 23:50.580
Seriously.

23:51.900 --> 23:52.510
You guys talk.

23:52.510 --> 23:53.110
We will.

23:53.350 --> 23:53.880
Be careful.

23:53.880 --> 23:55.140
Don't talk nonsense.

23:56.750 --> 23:57.830
Sorry for the trouble.

23:57.830 --> 23:58.420
Sorry for the trouble.

23:58.420 --> 24:00.090
It's okay. No problem.

24:00.900 --> 24:02.030
The song "Here Comes the Post Troika"

24:02.030 --> 24:03.950
is a Russian song, right?

24:04.030 --> 24:04.680
Yes.

24:04.850 --> 24:06.220
Why? Do you like singing this song?

24:06.220 --> 24:11.330
Snow and ice are covering the Volga River.

24:11.420 --> 24:13.370
On the icy river...

24:14.030 --> 24:15.230
Let's sing together!

24:17.140 --> 24:19.180
Earlier inside,

24:19.290 --> 24:21.330
do you think...

24:21.880 --> 24:22.440
I...

24:22.500 --> 24:23.160
I talked too much

24:23.160 --> 24:24.440
and was too nervous

24:24.440 --> 24:25.700
when I was with Sophia?

24:25.830 --> 24:26.290
No.

24:26.290 --> 24:27.830
You did great just now.

24:28.590 --> 24:29.320
That's good.

24:29.640 --> 24:30.920
That joke Liangliang made

24:30.920 --> 24:31.570
was completely inappropriate.

24:31.570 --> 24:32.200
How could he joke like that?

24:32.200 --> 24:33.640
Our pure friendship

24:33.640 --> 24:34.570
could have been shattered

24:34.570 --> 24:36.000
by his joke.

24:36.510 --> 24:37.380
I'll bring Liangliang out.

24:37.380 --> 24:38.050
No, no.

24:38.070 --> 24:39.550
Let them rest, Jun.

24:40.240 --> 24:40.780
Jun,

24:40.810 --> 24:42.900
are you really familiar with this area?

24:42.900 --> 24:43.750
Of course.

24:43.900 --> 24:44.640
Actually, in Russia,

24:44.640 --> 24:46.090
there are many Chinese businessmen.

24:46.090 --> 24:46.610
Wherever I go,

24:46.610 --> 24:47.860
people show me some respect.

24:47.860 --> 24:48.290
Alright.

24:48.290 --> 24:49.510
You see? Whenever asked
to do some work, Liangliang

24:49.510 --> 24:50.830
always complains
that his back or butt hurts.

24:50.830 --> 24:51.700
Unlike you.

24:52.200 --> 24:53.920
Although you're an arts student,

24:53.920 --> 24:56.180
you don't look tired
from the journey at all.

24:56.180 --> 24:56.940
I'm alright.

24:57.960 --> 24:58.610
To be honest,

24:58.610 --> 25:00.350
when Liangliang took out

25:00.350 --> 25:01.660
that stack of your business cards,

25:01.660 --> 25:03.170
I still hadn't figured out

25:03.200 --> 25:04.740
what kind of person you were.

25:04.740 --> 25:06.350
Now you know what kind of person I am?

25:06.350 --> 25:08.010
You have many good qualities.

25:08.330 --> 25:10.160
Just as many as the bad ones I have.

25:10.160 --> 25:11.410
Get in the car. I'll tell you.

25:11.410 --> 25:11.960
Okay.

25:12.200 --> 25:14.660
Are we talking about
your good or bad qualities?

25:14.660 --> 25:16.190
I'll tell you all of them.

25:17.030 --> 25:18.250
The main point is that...

25:18.250 --> 25:18.940
it's been a long time

25:18.940 --> 25:20.240
since I saw Sophia last time.

25:20.240 --> 25:21.310
I was so happy to see her.

25:21.310 --> 25:21.900
When you're all alone

25:21.900 --> 25:23.230
doing business abroad,

25:24.420 --> 25:25.160
honestly,

25:25.450 --> 25:26.480
sometimes

25:27.400 --> 25:29.110
you need a companion, you know?

25:29.110 --> 25:30.530
I'm happy

25:30.530 --> 25:32.060
to be working with you guys.

25:45.550 --> 25:46.980
We sold another 20 pairs at once.

25:46.980 --> 25:48.580
Check it. It should be right.

25:49.310 --> 25:50.290
What are you doing here?

25:50.290 --> 25:51.940
That guy from Shandong
went to the restroom.

25:51.940 --> 25:53.400
He asked me
to watch his stall for a while.

25:53.400 --> 25:54.050
You're so stupid.

25:54.050 --> 25:54.850
You just got deceived.

25:54.850 --> 25:55.550
He went out for a stroll

25:55.550 --> 25:56.140
and made you watch his stall.

25:56.140 --> 25:56.940
Did he pay you?

25:57.110 --> 25:58.440
Aren't we all from the same place?

25:58.440 --> 25:59.370
These things...

25:59.830 --> 26:01.260
are selling so well here.

26:01.310 --> 26:02.160
Should we get some more

26:02.160 --> 26:03.270
after we sell out?

26:03.350 --> 26:03.900
These things

26:03.900 --> 26:05.290
are a necessity in this season.

26:05.290 --> 26:06.940
They won't be worth much in a month.

26:06.940 --> 26:08.010
It's not worth the train tickets

26:08.010 --> 26:09.110
to make another trip.

26:09.110 --> 26:09.810
Jun.

26:09.920 --> 26:11.700
Looks like those leather jackets
are selling well.

26:11.700 --> 26:13.700
They make much more money than we do.

26:13.920 --> 26:14.430
Yes.

26:14.500 --> 26:16.170
But they have a high cost.

26:16.350 --> 26:17.690
And they're heavy.

26:17.790 --> 26:18.980
You know, each of us

26:18.980 --> 26:19.750
has a limit

26:19.750 --> 26:20.920
on the duty-free weight

26:20.920 --> 26:21.900
we can bring in here to sell.

26:21.900 --> 26:23.920
So selling in large quantities
actually makes more.

26:23.920 --> 26:25.230
I've calculated.

26:25.530 --> 26:26.330
Their best-selling stall

26:26.330 --> 26:27.930
makes about the same as ours.

26:28.830 --> 26:29.900
Good stuff.

26:29.980 --> 26:31.220
-Good stuff. Good stuff.
-Good stuff.

26:31.220 --> 26:31.900
Good stuff.

26:32.870 --> 26:34.410
Good stuff.

26:34.640 --> 26:36.040
Thermal underwear here.

26:36.380 --> 26:37.160
You want one?

26:37.530 --> 26:38.420
This one looks good.

26:38.420 --> 26:39.550
It looks good on you.

26:39.550 --> 26:40.640
The size is right, too.

26:40.640 --> 26:41.170
This one.

26:41.200 --> 26:41.660
If you wear it,

26:41.660 --> 26:43.590
you'll find a boyfriend in no time.

26:45.460 --> 26:46.350
Good stuff. Good stuff.

26:46.350 --> 26:47.680
Good stuff. Good stuff.

26:48.090 --> 26:49.050
Okay, thank you.

26:49.050 --> 26:49.590
Bye-bye.

26:53.850 --> 26:55.010
Get me a jacket.

26:55.940 --> 26:57.400
I told you these sell well.

26:57.660 --> 26:58.760
Keep the change.

26:58.850 --> 26:59.570
Come again.

27:00.510 --> 27:01.570
Thank you.

27:01.590 --> 27:02.700
Goodbye.

27:02.880 --> 27:03.540
Good stuff.

27:04.460 --> 27:04.960
Jun.

27:05.700 --> 27:06.570
I think we can do better

27:06.570 --> 27:08.000
if we pair up

27:08.030 --> 27:08.740
with the leather jacket seller

27:08.740 --> 27:09.900
across the street.

27:10.610 --> 27:11.920
I noticed that too.

27:13.440 --> 27:15.090
Do you think it would be better

27:15.090 --> 27:16.090
if we sell in sets?

27:16.550 --> 27:17.620
For example,

27:17.830 --> 27:19.250
a leather jacket with jeans,

27:19.250 --> 27:20.270
or an inner shirt,

27:20.610 --> 27:21.900
a hat, or a scarf, etc.

27:21.960 --> 27:23.020
We could make more.

27:23.240 --> 27:25.380
The purchase price is high,
so the cost is high.

27:25.380 --> 27:26.000
The four of us

27:26.000 --> 27:27.780
didn't put much money in total.

27:27.920 --> 27:29.330
If we purchase them,

27:29.460 --> 27:30.420
and they sell well, that's fine.

27:30.420 --> 27:31.010
But if they don't sell,

27:31.010 --> 27:32.660
won't our money be wasted?

27:32.900 --> 27:34.110
Did you two forget

27:34.110 --> 27:35.510
about the Maradona jerseys?

27:35.510 --> 27:37.370
They're still piled up in my room.

27:37.370 --> 27:37.960
Shut up.

27:37.960 --> 27:39.760
Why did you have to bring that up?

27:40.180 --> 27:40.900
True.

27:41.310 --> 27:43.420
Stockpiling is too risky.

27:43.500 --> 27:45.230
We've made a lot today.

27:45.590 --> 27:47.810
Let's find a place to eat first, shall we?

27:47.810 --> 27:49.000
We can sell the rest tomorrow.

27:49.000 --> 27:49.960
Look at you.

27:50.200 --> 27:51.220
You do no work,

27:51.440 --> 27:52.700
but your mouth is like a bottomless pit—

27:52.700 --> 27:53.300
so greedy.

27:53.350 --> 27:54.290
You just want to eat
when you make some money.

27:54.290 --> 27:55.300
How about this?

27:55.640 --> 27:57.000
You guys go eat.

27:57.440 --> 27:59.160
I'll sell these goods for a while longer.

27:59.160 --> 28:00.690
We'll meet at home tonight.

28:02.010 --> 28:03.480
Can you find your way back?

28:06.270 --> 28:06.870
The route.

28:08.980 --> 28:10.880
So you'll stay here and keep selling?

28:10.880 --> 28:11.660
Then I'll take this idiot

28:11.660 --> 28:12.410
to get a bite.

28:12.510 --> 28:13.070
Later,

28:13.070 --> 28:14.530
remember to pack all these goods up.

28:14.530 --> 28:16.310
-You can drive the car back.
-Okay. Don't worry.

28:16.310 --> 28:17.240
We'll walk back.

28:17.250 --> 28:18.980
Zhuang Zhuang, are you hungry?

28:21.140 --> 28:22.640
Then just go with them.

28:22.740 --> 28:23.980
Okay, let's go.

28:24.240 --> 28:24.700
Bye.

28:24.810 --> 28:25.370
Bye.

28:25.800 --> 28:28.310
Will you be okay here alone?

28:28.680 --> 28:30.920
He's all about money now.

28:31.070 --> 28:31.620
Let's go.

28:31.740 --> 28:32.200
How about this?

28:32.200 --> 28:33.270
I'll stay here with him.

28:33.270 --> 28:33.700
Okay.

28:34.030 --> 28:34.680
Let's go.

28:34.750 --> 28:35.610
Okay, then you stay.

28:35.610 --> 28:37.330
No, I'm hungry. I'm hungry.

28:37.350 --> 28:38.300
Thank you!

28:39.750 --> 28:40.980
Stay safe!

28:41.570 --> 28:42.740
Have you ever had borscht?

28:42.740 --> 28:43.540
No, I haven't.

28:46.970 --> 28:48.500
Sir, may I ask you something?

28:48.500 --> 28:49.480
I just saw someone

28:49.480 --> 28:51.280
trading something for a kettle.

28:51.640 --> 28:52.500
Is it possible to barter

28:52.500 --> 28:53.750
in this market?

28:53.880 --> 28:54.290
Yes.

28:54.380 --> 28:55.980
As long as it's easy to sell and valuable,

28:55.980 --> 28:56.910
you can trade it.

28:57.310 --> 28:58.290
So I can trade with anything?

28:58.290 --> 28:59.410
Yes, you can.

28:59.770 --> 29:00.720
Thanks.

29:00.790 --> 29:01.720
You're welcome.

29:03.510 --> 29:05.440
I'm all about money?

29:06.090 --> 29:07.870
I'm an opportunist?

29:08.090 --> 29:10.150
Just wait and see how I make a fortune.

29:10.220 --> 29:11.070
Xu Shengli.

29:13.680 --> 29:15.160
You didn't go with them?

29:15.920 --> 29:17.450
Still dwelling on the past?

29:17.900 --> 29:19.550
No.

29:21.160 --> 29:22.530
You have

29:22.590 --> 29:24.070
such a tiny mind.

29:25.530 --> 29:27.030
So you didn't go with them

29:27.030 --> 29:29.140
because you were worried about me?

29:31.310 --> 29:31.940
I figured

29:31.940 --> 29:33.600
you were thinking about that.

29:34.640 --> 29:35.590
I wasn't.

29:35.620 --> 29:37.550
I wasn't thinking about anything.

29:48.830 --> 29:50.090
This is called a match.

29:51.920 --> 29:53.920
So now you know how to match clothes?

29:54.940 --> 29:55.510
Well,

29:55.510 --> 29:56.960
spending so much time with you,

29:56.960 --> 29:58.090
it rubbed off on me.

30:01.350 --> 30:03.110
You're always the best.

30:05.810 --> 30:06.850
Do we still match?

30:08.110 --> 30:09.920
We match perfectly.

30:10.940 --> 30:12.140
Who matches with you?

30:12.720 --> 30:15.560
Then who matches with you?

30:15.750 --> 30:16.740
I mean the jeans

30:16.750 --> 30:18.810
and the leather jackets—they match.

30:19.880 --> 30:21.090
Yeah, they matche.

30:23.000 --> 30:25.000
Your hands are so red from the cold.

30:38.350 --> 30:39.550
Here, take my gloves.

30:40.110 --> 30:40.440
Here.

30:41.960 --> 30:43.270
Left hand.

30:44.660 --> 30:47.890
Put it in.

30:48.070 --> 30:49.040
This one.

30:49.700 --> 30:50.160
Here.

30:50.940 --> 30:52.200
Put it in.

31:01.810 --> 31:02.430
How is it?

31:11.030 --> 31:11.510
Eight.

31:12.000 --> 31:12.530
Nine.

31:12.830 --> 31:13.440
Ten.

31:13.850 --> 31:14.330
Jack.

31:14.850 --> 31:15.310
Queen.

31:17.220 --> 31:17.680
Come on.

31:17.830 --> 31:19.550
You guys just came back?

31:19.680 --> 31:20.810
What were you doing?

31:21.180 --> 31:22.200
We didn't sell anything

31:22.200 --> 31:23.660
and brought them all back.

31:25.090 --> 31:26.480
Look how excited you are.

31:26.480 --> 31:28.010
Is there a baby in this sack?

31:28.790 --> 31:29.390
Hold this.

31:30.000 --> 31:31.060
What are you doing?

31:33.380 --> 31:34.310
How does it look?

31:34.640 --> 31:35.310
Look good?

31:35.900 --> 31:36.880
You are tall

31:36.900 --> 31:37.740
and handsome.

31:37.790 --> 31:39.160
You look good in anything.

31:39.160 --> 31:39.740
Not bad.

31:40.180 --> 31:41.570
Did you two go shopping this afternoon?

31:41.570 --> 31:42.240
No.

31:42.770 --> 31:44.830
We went to get some samples.

31:47.550 --> 31:50.080
You're still thinking about
this afternoon?

31:50.270 --> 31:52.020
Yes, it looks good.

31:52.110 --> 31:53.530
But the cost is too high.

31:53.570 --> 31:54.440
Didn't I tell you?

31:54.440 --> 31:56.070
We don't have enough capital.

31:56.070 --> 31:57.330
We don't need capital.

31:57.680 --> 31:58.550
We can just use our goods

31:58.550 --> 31:59.530
to trade with them.

31:59.530 --> 32:00.990
Is there such a good thing?

32:01.110 --> 32:01.740
Wait.

32:02.000 --> 32:03.290
It's free for now.

32:03.310 --> 32:04.220
When the goods are sold,

32:04.220 --> 32:05.480
we have to make up the difference.

32:05.480 --> 32:06.720
Make up the difference?

32:06.720 --> 32:07.220
What does that mean?

32:07.220 --> 32:08.110
I don't understand.

32:08.110 --> 32:09.110
Here's the thing.

32:09.640 --> 32:11.570
Our goods have a low profit margin,

32:11.750 --> 32:12.590
but they sell in large quantities.

32:12.590 --> 32:13.590
We make quick money.

32:13.590 --> 32:15.440
Of course
they're willing to trade with us.

32:15.440 --> 32:16.530
We two were thinking

32:16.530 --> 32:17.920
of taking their leather jackets

32:17.920 --> 32:19.230
and our jeans,

32:19.530 --> 32:20.720
then matching them with sweaters

32:20.720 --> 32:22.050
to sell as sets.

32:23.110 --> 32:24.000
We found out

32:24.200 --> 32:25.330
that the market here

32:25.350 --> 32:27.080
takes goods in bales.

32:27.400 --> 32:28.750
They have to sort them out
when they get back,

32:28.750 --> 32:30.440
and there are many defective products.

32:30.440 --> 32:31.770
Those individual customers in the market

32:31.770 --> 32:33.110
have to spend time and energy

32:33.110 --> 32:34.510
matching and selecting.

32:34.640 --> 32:36.170
So we two came up with an idea

32:36.440 --> 32:37.570
to match our clothes

32:37.680 --> 32:39.380
into so-called suits to sell.

32:39.440 --> 32:39.940
Right.

32:40.200 --> 32:40.570
We two

32:40.570 --> 32:41.830
have looked around the market.

32:41.830 --> 32:42.830
There are only a few stores

32:42.830 --> 32:43.810
doing this.

32:43.810 --> 32:44.310
And

32:44.720 --> 32:46.380
they sell them at a very high price.

32:46.380 --> 32:48.440
As long as we are a little cheaper
than them,

32:48.440 --> 32:49.570
we will earn more than we do now.

32:49.570 --> 32:51.590
Then we go and sign an agreement

32:51.700 --> 32:52.550
with these merchants.

32:52.550 --> 32:54.150
After these things are sold,

32:54.240 --> 32:55.790
we will make up the difference to them.

32:55.790 --> 32:56.440
That's it.

32:56.680 --> 32:58.440
Just tell me one thing.

32:58.510 --> 33:00.960
-Can it make money?
-Yes! Very much.

33:01.070 --> 33:02.700
Then we should definitely do it.

33:02.700 --> 33:04.960
Who wouldn't do something profitable?

33:05.110 --> 33:05.700
When I saw you guys

33:05.700 --> 33:06.840
in Beijing,

33:06.920 --> 33:08.450
I felt that you looked like

33:09.270 --> 33:10.050
you could make money.

33:10.050 --> 33:11.480
You look like money-makers.

33:11.480 --> 33:12.110
It shows on your faces.

33:12.110 --> 33:12.910
Wait a minute.

33:13.980 --> 33:14.800
In Beijing,

33:14.850 --> 33:17.510
didn't you say it was the three of us?

33:18.220 --> 33:19.810
Something shows on your face too,

33:19.810 --> 33:22.470
but not money.

33:22.590 --> 33:23.390
Stop talking.

33:23.400 --> 33:24.530
A saxophone shows on my face.

33:24.530 --> 33:25.660
Whatever you say.

33:26.110 --> 33:27.480
I understand it now.

33:27.880 --> 33:29.610
But the premise is based on

33:29.610 --> 33:30.180
the situation that our suits

33:30.180 --> 33:31.400
can all be sold.

33:31.510 --> 33:32.440
If they can't be sold,

33:32.440 --> 33:33.830
we won't even have the thermal underwear.

33:33.830 --> 33:34.250
Yes.

33:34.960 --> 33:35.850
Because there are risks,

33:35.850 --> 33:37.310
we only made samples.

33:37.420 --> 33:38.240
We only discussed it

33:38.240 --> 33:39.900
orally with them.

33:40.270 --> 33:41.200
After all,

33:41.250 --> 33:43.110
the four of us are working together.

33:43.110 --> 33:44.010
So we had to come back

33:44.010 --> 33:45.540
and discuss it with you two.

33:45.640 --> 33:46.870
You three discuss it.

33:47.070 --> 33:48.070
Don't include me.

33:48.290 --> 33:50.770
I don't care how much I earn.

33:51.110 --> 33:52.170
As long as you three

33:52.590 --> 33:54.190
can take me, Tao Liangliang,

33:54.640 --> 33:56.320
back to Beijing.

33:57.770 --> 33:59.880
You three dumped the problem on me.

34:04.660 --> 34:05.940
But do you think

34:06.030 --> 34:07.010
your Mr. Lucky

34:07.050 --> 34:08.780
is someone who backs down?

34:09.360 --> 34:10.190
No.

34:10.480 --> 34:13.020
I have to face
the difficulties head-on, right?

34:13.020 --> 34:13.750
Look at this.

34:13.920 --> 34:15.690
I didn't even bomb your 3 twos!

34:15.780 --> 34:17.310
Look how lucky I am!

34:17.360 --> 34:18.510
Four, five, six, seven, eight!

34:18.510 --> 34:20.590
I could have won in a second!

34:21.050 --> 34:23.190
For such a thing, let's do it!

34:23.260 --> 34:24.010
Let's do it!

34:24.010 --> 34:24.469
Come on!

34:24.510 --> 34:24.969
Come on!

34:25.280 --> 34:25.900
Let's do it!

34:25.900 --> 34:27.360
-Let's do it!
-Let's do it!

34:27.730 --> 34:28.389
Let's do it!

34:29.070 --> 34:30.270
Let's shout a slogan.

34:30.340 --> 34:31.130
It's called,

34:31.190 --> 34:32.110
"Life is about striving."

34:32.110 --> 34:32.630
I'll shout 'life'.

34:32.630 --> 34:33.440
-And you shout "is about striving."
-Okay.

34:33.440 --> 34:33.840
Okay!

34:33.840 --> 34:34.320
Life!

34:34.360 --> 34:36.380
Is about striving!

34:39.500 --> 34:40.570
Clothes!

34:40.820 --> 34:41.610
This car is borrowed.

34:41.610 --> 34:43.170
It's borrowed! Don't break it!

34:43.170 --> 34:44.600
Alright, come down!

34:44.690 --> 34:45.480
So noisy.

34:45.570 --> 34:47.300
Good stuff!

34:47.350 --> 34:48.400
This car is borrowed.

34:48.400 --> 34:49.909
Don't yell here.

34:50.070 --> 34:51.280
Then where should we yell?

34:51.280 --> 34:52.080
Go over there.

34:52.210 --> 34:53.670
Find customers on the street.

34:53.670 --> 34:54.550
Be careful.

34:54.960 --> 34:56.090
Don't be too restrained.

34:56.090 --> 34:56.570
Okay.

34:56.710 --> 34:57.640
Make some noise.

34:57.690 --> 34:58.960
I guarantee to complete the task!

34:58.960 --> 34:59.490
Hurry up.

34:59.710 --> 35:00.420
Then let's go.

35:00.420 --> 35:01.480
Let's go, let's go.

35:01.670 --> 35:02.610
Get more customers!

35:02.610 --> 35:03.500
Good stuff!

35:03.710 --> 35:04.540
Thank you!

35:04.710 --> 35:06.410
Leather jackets!

35:06.480 --> 35:07.140
Good stuff!

35:07.230 --> 35:08.230
Leather jackets!

35:08.280 --> 35:10.050
Good stuff! Good stuff!

35:10.110 --> 35:12.630
Leather jackets! Leather jackets!

35:12.690 --> 35:13.400
Leather jackets!

35:13.400 --> 35:15.150
Leather jackets! Good stuff!

35:15.420 --> 35:16.360
Good stuff!

35:16.460 --> 35:17.610
Leather jackets! Leather jackets!

35:17.610 --> 35:19.230
Leather jackets! Leather jackets!

35:19.230 --> 35:20.780
-Good stuff! Good stuff!
-Leather jackets!

35:20.780 --> 35:22.280
Good stuff! Good stuff!

35:22.590 --> 35:24.080
Good stuff! Good stuff!

35:24.190 --> 35:25.190
Leather jackets!

35:25.260 --> 35:26.570
Good stuff! Good stuff!

35:26.570 --> 35:27.170
Leather jackets!

35:27.170 --> 35:27.710
Leather jackets!

35:27.710 --> 35:28.820
Jeans! Jeans!

35:28.920 --> 35:29.710
Good stuff. Good stuff.

35:29.710 --> 35:30.740
We have new ones!

35:30.820 --> 35:31.480
New ones!

35:31.590 --> 35:32.550
Here, over here!

35:32.550 --> 35:33.610
The new ones! Look!

35:33.610 --> 35:34.430
Move forward.

35:34.960 --> 35:36.130
Thank you!

35:37.030 --> 35:38.900
Leather jackets, leather jackets.

35:38.900 --> 35:39.960
Buy a set for your sister.

35:39.960 --> 35:41.280
Good stuff! Good stuff!

35:41.280 --> 35:42.420
Jun! Jun!

35:43.110 --> 35:43.970
So many people.

35:45.340 --> 35:45.860
Come on.

35:45.920 --> 35:47.050
What are they doing?

35:48.320 --> 35:49.920
They must have brought them here.

35:49.920 --> 35:50.500
So many people.

35:50.500 --> 35:51.230
It's a bit scary.

35:51.230 --> 35:52.630
Get the clothes. Come on.

35:52.940 --> 35:53.650
Good stuff!

35:53.650 --> 35:54.570
Are they here to buy things from us?

35:54.570 --> 35:55.760
-Really?
-Yes.

35:55.780 --> 35:56.770
Good! Good!

35:56.880 --> 35:57.840
Good stuff! Good stuff!

35:57.840 --> 35:58.940
Jeans! Jeans!

35:59.030 --> 36:00.480
These jeans look great!

36:00.650 --> 36:01.150
Miss.

36:01.210 --> 36:02.210
Miss, look at these jeans.

36:02.210 --> 36:02.480
Good stuff.

36:02.480 --> 36:02.920
Okay?

36:02.980 --> 36:03.360
Yeah.

36:03.500 --> 36:04.250
How much?

36:05.230 --> 36:05.870
Sold!

36:05.960 --> 36:07.140
Sold!

36:07.230 --> 36:08.460
-Sold?
-Sold!

36:09.920 --> 36:10.570
Is this it?

36:10.650 --> 36:12.300
This isn't enough.

36:12.480 --> 36:13.510
Jeans.

36:13.710 --> 36:14.410
No, no, no.

36:14.460 --> 36:16.890
Yes, jeans.

36:16.940 --> 36:17.480
Right.

36:17.900 --> 36:18.860
Okay.

36:18.860 --> 36:19.690
Over here.

36:19.900 --> 36:22.300
Make way. They're cold. Let's talk inside.

36:22.360 --> 36:23.760
Let's talk inside. Come.

36:30.260 --> 36:31.760
Don't run! Don't run!

36:32.340 --> 36:33.740
The price is negotiable!

36:33.920 --> 36:35.550
Seriously!

36:35.650 --> 36:36.690
Give the money to her!

36:36.690 --> 36:37.590
Give the money to her!

36:37.590 --> 36:38.800
Good stuff!

36:40.050 --> 36:40.980
This looks good.

36:42.780 --> 36:44.460
Just use hand gestures.

36:44.610 --> 36:45.260
Which one do you want?

36:45.260 --> 36:46.170
Are these jeans okay?

36:46.170 --> 36:46.900
This one. Is it pretty?

36:46.900 --> 36:47.420
This one.

36:47.420 --> 36:48.620
It doesn't look good.

36:48.820 --> 36:50.000
This old lady is quite picky.

36:50.000 --> 36:50.760
This one.

36:50.780 --> 36:51.090
This one looks good.

36:51.090 --> 36:52.130
Do you think they can take away

36:52.130 --> 36:53.570
the money they earned here?

36:53.570 --> 36:55.110
Of course not.

36:55.300 --> 36:56.040
Looks good!

36:56.610 --> 36:58.570
Good stuff! Good stuff!

36:58.590 --> 37:00.420
This much!

37:00.590 --> 37:02.230
This much! For the whole set.

37:02.280 --> 37:04.110
Give the money to...

37:04.320 --> 37:05.090
to Zhuang Zhuang.

37:05.090 --> 37:05.950
Take the money!

37:06.010 --> 37:07.410
This one looks good.

37:07.500 --> 37:09.180
This one looks very good.

37:33.570 --> 37:34.430
Zhuang Zhuang!

37:35.920 --> 37:36.850
Zhuang Zhuang!

37:54.500 --> 37:55.210
Xu Shengli!

37:56.840 --> 37:57.900
What are you doing?

37:59.590 --> 38:01.360
I am playing with snowballs.

38:05.650 --> 38:07.710
I knocked on your door for a long time,

38:07.780 --> 38:09.040
but you weren't there.

38:09.260 --> 38:10.940
So you're here having a snowball fight.

38:10.940 --> 38:12.260
I was wondering
why I kept throwing it at your window

38:12.260 --> 38:13.820
and you didn't react.

38:13.980 --> 38:15.500
Look whose room this is.

38:16.980 --> 38:18.180
Isn't this your room?

38:19.010 --> 38:21.490
Then... this is my room.

38:22.360 --> 38:23.340
Hurry up! Let's go!

38:23.340 --> 38:23.900
Let's go.

38:23.940 --> 38:26.600
Liangliang... Liangliang is sleeping.
Hurry.

38:35.980 --> 38:36.800
Who is it?

38:37.190 --> 38:39.610
I didn't expect it
to go so smoothly this time.

38:39.610 --> 38:40.300
Yeah.

38:40.670 --> 38:41.870
It feels like a dream.

39:07.670 --> 39:08.510
It sounds so good.

39:08.510 --> 39:09.200
Thank you.

39:27.190 --> 39:27.800
Bye-bye.

39:31.380 --> 39:32.440
Careful, it's hot.

39:32.820 --> 39:33.420
Thank you.

39:36.550 --> 39:37.680
I'll peel it for you.

39:39.630 --> 39:40.690
Careful, it's hot.

39:40.710 --> 39:41.620
It is a bit hot.

39:41.920 --> 39:42.520
It's fine.

39:52.070 --> 39:52.590
Okay.

39:53.190 --> 39:54.120
Hold the bottom.

40:02.880 --> 40:03.480
A whistle?

40:05.000 --> 40:05.820
It's for you.

40:06.550 --> 40:07.900
I bought it at the train station.

40:07.900 --> 40:09.510
Just think of it as a souvenir.

40:09.510 --> 40:10.790
This is not a souvenir.

40:11.360 --> 40:12.380
It's an amulet.

40:18.360 --> 40:19.330
I get it.

40:19.760 --> 40:20.710
When I blow it,

40:20.710 --> 40:21.640
you will appear.

40:23.130 --> 40:23.850
Maybe.

40:30.460 --> 40:31.210
Alright.

40:31.260 --> 40:32.500
I'm right here, aren't I?

40:32.500 --> 40:33.750
I just want to blow it.

40:34.320 --> 40:35.900
Well... when I miss you...

40:35.900 --> 40:36.830
I can blow it too.

40:42.880 --> 40:44.280
Look at your frozen ears.

40:45.150 --> 40:47.280
You didn't wear a hat when you went out.

40:49.130 --> 40:50.690
What did you say?

40:54.980 --> 40:55.730
I said,

40:57.650 --> 40:59.280
I found that I quite like you.

41:04.820 --> 41:06.820
I didn't hear what you said clearly.

41:09.960 --> 41:11.260
I said the blood supply to your brain

41:11.260 --> 41:12.150
comes and goes.

41:13.630 --> 41:15.430
Didn't you say you quite like me?

41:30.300 --> 41:31.460
You don't know

41:31.460 --> 41:32.760
how happy I am.

41:32.800 --> 41:33.710
Just these past few days,

41:33.710 --> 41:34.360
I've brought in so many people

41:34.360 --> 41:35.690
that we could form a whole company.

41:35.690 --> 41:36.980
So it has nothing to do with me?

41:36.980 --> 41:37.890
It does.

41:37.980 --> 41:39.200
Just a little bit.

41:39.300 --> 41:40.510
I really didn't expect

41:40.510 --> 41:41.230
that besides me,

41:41.230 --> 41:42.420
Liangliang is also

41:42.420 --> 41:43.940
quite popular in Russia, right?

41:43.940 --> 41:44.300
Jun,

41:44.320 --> 41:44.920
our goods

41:44.920 --> 41:45.880
are almost sold out.

41:45.880 --> 41:46.880
What do we do next?

41:47.780 --> 41:49.460
I wanted to tell you guys earlier

41:49.460 --> 41:50.720
that the cost

41:51.000 --> 41:52.710
of restocking and exchanging goods locally

41:52.710 --> 41:53.440
was too high.

41:54.190 --> 41:54.980
I heard

41:55.190 --> 41:56.110
that in Vladivostek,

41:56.110 --> 41:56.860
they just got a batch

41:56.860 --> 41:57.800
of bulk clothing from China.

41:57.800 --> 41:58.710
It's Vladivostok.

41:58.710 --> 41:59.590
That's not important.

41:59.590 --> 42:00.650
You know what I mean.

42:00.650 --> 42:01.440
They got a batch

42:01.440 --> 42:02.650
of bulk Chinese clothing,

42:02.650 --> 42:03.920
and the quality is excellent.

42:03.920 --> 42:05.210
But I didn't dare to take the offer.

42:05.210 --> 42:05.710
Why?

42:05.760 --> 42:07.150
Because our sales volume wasn't that high,

42:07.150 --> 42:07.840
and we didn't have

42:07.840 --> 42:08.900
that much capital.

42:08.920 --> 42:09.580
But now that

42:09.710 --> 42:11.650
our sales
have gone up these past two days.

42:11.650 --> 42:12.170
Right?

42:12.260 --> 42:13.130
I calculated our earnings,

42:13.130 --> 42:14.260
and we have enough capital now.

42:14.260 --> 42:16.280
So I took the liberty

42:17.550 --> 42:18.900
of calling them today.

42:20.230 --> 42:22.130
I think we have a great chance

42:22.440 --> 42:23.440
to make big money.

42:25.010 --> 42:28.150
Mr. Lucky deserves his name.

42:29.050 --> 42:30.670
Find Mr. Lucky and be lucky!

42:30.670 --> 42:31.050
Right?

42:31.050 --> 42:31.630
175,000.

42:31.670 --> 42:31.960
Okay.

42:31.960 --> 42:33.160
Come on, let's drink.

42:35.650 --> 42:36.110
I'll go.

42:38.500 --> 42:39.760
Sophia is back, right?

42:41.030 --> 42:41.510
Hello.

42:42.150 --> 42:42.820
Hello.

42:43.480 --> 42:44.070
I am the one

42:44.070 --> 42:46.590
selling goods at the market lately.

42:47.050 --> 42:47.960
We're in the same business,

42:47.960 --> 42:49.190
and we're also compatriots.

42:49.190 --> 42:49.820
I'm Chinese.

42:49.820 --> 42:50.570
Hello.

42:50.630 --> 42:51.460
My surname is Du.

42:51.460 --> 42:52.440
Just call me Du.

42:53.550 --> 42:54.790
Can I help you?
